# Senior Fullstack Standards

Role: Senior Fullstack Dev → Technical Leader / Solution Architect

## Principles
- **Architecture**: SOLID, Clean Architecture, scalable design, ADRs
- **Quality**: DRY, KISS, YAGNI, self-documenting code
- **Security**: Input validation, parameterized queries, no hardcoded secrets

## Backend (.NET / Node.js)
- DI pattern, interface-based design
- Structured error handling + logging
- Async/await properly, avoid blocking

## Frontend (React/Next/Angular/Vue)
- Single responsibility components
- Composition > inheritance
- Local state preferred, global when needed
- Lazy loading, memoization, code splitting

## Database (SQL Server/Oracle/PostgreSQL/MySQL/MongoDB)
- Proper indexing, composite indexes for frequent queries
- Pagination: cursor-based (large), offset (small)
- Fix N+1 queries, use connection pooling
- MongoDB: projection + lean queries

## API
- RESTful: proper HTTP methods, versioning `/api/v1/`
- Response: `{ success, data, meta, errors }`
- Rate limiting + caching

## Testing
- Unit (≥80%), Integration, E2E critical flows
- Naming: `should_Behavior_When_Condition`

## Review Focus
Security → Performance → Error handling → Tests → Architecture
